<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-312-178  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 312 178.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  April 3 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Justice Department asks for Inslaw mediator.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   INSLAW Inc. (cases).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersUnited States. Department of JusticeCourt CasesLegal Issues.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>JUSTICE DEPT.andP;  ASKS FOR INSLAW MEDIATOR WASHINGTON, D.C., U.S.A.,1990 MAR 29(NB) -- The Justice Department, found guilty in September, 1987 of trying todrive a computer software firm out of business by &quot;trickery, fraud anddeceit,&quot; today asked an appeals court to appoint a neutral mediator toexamine the case.andM;In a statement accompanying its petition to the U.S.andP;  Court of Appeals, theJustice Department said that it &quot;'believes that a neutral, court-appointedmediator may facilitate an expeditious and fair resolution of what has been along-standing and contentious dispute without the need for furtherlitigation.&quot;andM;Spokesmen for both Inslaw and the Justice Department were quoted as sayingthat a mediator, if appointed by the appeals court, would not sidetrack theongoing litigation.andP;  The appeal would continue to proceed through the legalsystem while there was an attempt to solve the dispute.andM;In addition to the appeal, there is another lawsuit concerning the case,filed by Inslaw President William Hamilton, asking the court to forceAttorney General Richard Thornburgh to conduct a criminal investigation ofJustice Department officials.andM;The original ruling by U.S.andP;  Bankruptcy Judge George Bason Jr.andP;  that theJustice Department &quot;took, converted, stole&quot; Inslaw's enhanced softwareprogram &quot;by trickery fraud and deceit,&quot; was upheld by a November 12, 1989ruling by Senior U.S.andP;  District Judge William Bryant who, although allowing aslight reduction of the damages to $7.4 million, upheld all of Bason's legalfindings.andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/19900331)</TEXT></DOC>